Company Overview of HSBC Bank Plc



Snapshot People




Company Overview
HSBC Bank plc provides various banking products and services worldwide. It operates through Retail Banking and Wealth Management, Commercial Banking, Global Banking and Markets, and Global Private Banking segments. The company accepts various deposits, such as current, savings, and business bank accounts. Its loan products include personal, flexi, graduate, small and flexible business, enterprise finance guarantee, long and short-term, working capital, and import and export loans; commodity and structured trade, and receivables finance; mortgages; and overdrafts. The company also offers credit, debit, and corporate cards; investment funds and advisory services; and car, travel, home, student...
HSBC Bank plc provides various banking products and services worldwide. It operates through Retail Banking and Wealth Management, Commercial Banking, Global Banking and Markets, and Global Private Banking segments. The company accepts various deposits, such as current, savings, and business bank accounts. Its loan products include personal, flexi, graduate, small and flexible business, enterprise finance guarantee, long and short-term, working capital, and import and export loans; commodity and structured trade, and receivables finance; mortgages; and overdrafts. The company also offers credit, debit, and corporate cards; investment funds and advisory services; and car, travel, home, student, employers' and public liability, professional indemnity, van, block of flats, business loan protection, life, pet, and high value home insurance products. In addition, it provides import and export letters of credit, standby letters of credit, and import documentary credits; international money transfer, payment, account, and travel money services; clearing and foreign currency payments, foreign exchange risk management, invoice discounting, factoring, foreign exchange, mergers and acquisitions, investment management, transaction banking, and discretionary and brokerage services; import and export documentary collections, and guarantee services; liquidity management and wealth solutions; and risk management services, as well as Internet, mobile, telephone, and branch banking services. The company serves small enterprises, government, and corporate and institutional clients, as well as high net worth individuals and families. As of December 31, 2016, it operated 964 branches in the United Kingdom; and 13 located in the Isle of Man and the Channel Islands. The company was founded in 1880 and is based in London, the United Kingdom. HSBC Bank plc is a subsidiary of HSBC Holdings plc.
